00:09:51,488 --> 00:09:52,905
Okay, but arming yourself
isn't enough.

250
00:09:52,956 --> 00:09:54,573
We need
to actually do something.

251
00:09:54,624 --> 00:09:57,326
Harvey told me
to sit tight.

252
00:09:57,360 --> 00:09:59,044
That's exactly
what I'm gonna do.

253
00:09:59,078 --> 00:10:02,197
Right, that's because
Harvey's life isn't on the line.

254
00:10:02,215 --> 00:10:04,967
Ours is.

255
00:10:08,371 --> 00:10:09,388
Ours?

256
00:10:09,422 --> 00:10:12,508
Mike, I am not moving in
with you

257
00:10:12,542 --> 00:10:16,061
because I need
a new place to live.

258
00:10:16,095 --> 00:10:18,597
Okay, so what do you think
we should do?

259
00:10:18,648 --> 00:10:21,150
What's gonna make him believe
that you went to Harvard?

260
00:10:21,184 --> 00:10:22,901
Well, if my transcript,
diploma,

261
00:10:22,936 --> 00:10:24,987
and the job you can only get
by having attended Harvard

262
00:10:25,021 --> 00:10:26,822
aren't enough,
I'm not really sure what is.

263
00:10:26,856 --> 00:10:28,657
Well, there's got to be
something you can say.

264
00:10:28,691 --> 00:10:30,725
Look, Rachel,
you know Louis.

265
00:10:30,743 --> 00:10:31,743
The more I try and deny it,

266
00:10:31,778 --> 00:10:34,613
the more
he's gonna come after me.

267
00:10:34,664 --> 00:10:36,248
I can't believe this.

268
00:10:36,282 --> 00:10:37,749
He is not gonna be happy
until he has

269
00:10:37,784 --> 00:10:40,919
a signed full confession
proving he was right.

270
00:10:43,289 --> 00:10:46,875
You're right.

271
00:10:46,909 --> 00:10:50,512
And that's exactly
what I'm gonna give him.

272
00:10:50,547 --> 00:10:51,930
Come on.

273
00:10:51,965 --> 00:10:53,348
It's all
fairly straightforward.

274
00:10:53,383 --> 00:10:55,017
The company
shouldn't be affected.

275
00:10:55,051 --> 00:10:57,219
Tim can continue
with the day-to-day

276
00:10:57,253 --> 00:10:59,254
while this works
its way through probate.

277
00:10:59,272 --> 00:11:03,358
Well, the day-to-day's
going to change.

278
00:11:03,393 --> 00:11:06,028
- How so?
- We have an offer from Pryzen.

279
00:11:06,062 --> 00:11:07,362
You want to sell
the company?

280
00:11:07,397 --> 00:11:11,149
I want to accept an offer.

281
00:11:11,201 --> 00:11:13,569
Well, that was fast.

282
00:11:13,603 --> 00:11:14,953
Excuse me?

283
00:11:14,988 --> 00:11:16,488
What Jessica is saying is

284
00:11:16,539 --> 00:11:18,790
Pryzen didn't waste
any time swooping in.

285
00:11:18,825 --> 00:11:20,993
No, what I'm saying is,

286
00:11:21,044 --> 00:11:22,277
before we authorize anything,

287
00:11:22,295 --> 00:11:24,496
we need to evaluate
if this is even a good idea.

288
00:11:24,547 --> 00:11:25,998
I don't see why.

289
00:11:26,049 --> 00:11:28,050
Our general counsel thinks
it's a good idea, and I agree.

290
00:11:28,084 --> 00:11:31,620
And I'm the one who's inheriting
the majority of the company,

291
00:11:31,638 --> 00:11:33,589
so it's my decision.
Actually, it isn't.

292
00:11:33,623 --> 00:11:34,923
What are you talking about?

293
00:11:34,957 --> 00:11:38,010
My job is to see that
Quentin's wishes are fulfilled.

294
00:11:38,061 --> 00:11:39,678
Are you implying
that you know his wishes

295
00:11:39,729 --> 00:11:41,346
better than I do?

296
00:11:41,397 --> 00:11:42,797
I'm implying
he's not dead a week,

297
00:11:42,815 --> 00:11:44,733
and you want to strip his name
off the door and into oblivion.

298
00:11:44,767 --> 00:11:46,801
What I want to do
is put the drug

299
00:11:46,819 --> 00:11:48,237
that he dedicated
his life to

300
00:11:48,271 --> 00:11:51,657
in the hands of a company
with the resources to finish it.

301
00:11:51,691 --> 00:11:54,693
And I was there when he worked
for companies like this.

302
00:11:54,744 --> 00:11:57,829
And he hated them, which is why
he went out on his own.

303
00:11:57,864 --> 00:11:59,197
You were there?

304
00:11:59,249 --> 00:12:02,251
Well, that's not how I heard
the story.

305
00:12:02,285 --> 00:12:05,871
All right,
we're not doing this.

306
00:12:05,922 --> 00:12:08,156
You want to sell your shares?
No one's saying you can't.

307
00:12:08,174 --> 00:12:12,010
But we have a responsibility
to evaluate it.

308
00:12:12,045 --> 00:12:14,846
Remember when you said
you'd try to be conciliatory?

309
00:12:14,881 --> 00:12:16,214
I never said that.

310
00:12:16,266 --> 00:12:18,600
Well, you should have,
'cause you sure couldn't

311
00:12:18,635 --> 00:12:20,185
keep the personal out of it.

312
00:12:20,219 --> 00:12:21,353
I didn't think
they were gonna come at me

313
00:12:21,387 --> 00:12:22,354
with all that stuff.

314
00:12:22,388 --> 00:12:23,505
They weren't coming at you.

315
00:12:23,523 --> 00:12:25,107
They were coming
with a proposal.

316
00:12:25,141 --> 00:12:29,778
Do you really think
that offer came out of thin air?

317
00:12:29,812 --> 00:12:31,563
I think it's possible
they waited to pounce.

318
00:12:31,614 --> 00:12:32,847
It's also possible

319
00:12:32,865 --> 00:12:34,900
that Lisa and Tim
put this in motion

320
00:12:34,951 --> 00:12:36,985
while Quentin was lying
in his hospital bed.

321
00:12:37,019 --> 00:12:39,871
And what if they did?
Is that really our business?

322
00:12:39,906 --> 00:12:42,658
Jessica, I understand
how hard this is for you,

323
00:12:42,692 --> 00:12:44,826
but his legacy is this drug.

324
00:12:44,860 --> 00:12:47,079
It's not about whose name
is on the company that makes it.

325
00:12:47,130 --> 00:12:49,197
You're saying
you agree with Lisa.

326
00:12:49,215 --> 00:12:51,583
I'm saying to you now
what I tried to tell you before.

327
00:12:51,634 --> 00:12:54,920
This is personal for you.
It's not personal for me.

328
00:12:54,971 --> 00:12:58,924
So before we take another step,
let me evaluate this offer.

329
00:13:03,563 --> 00:13:04,546
You're right.

330
00:13:04,564 --> 00:13:07,849
I lied to you.

331
00:13:07,883 --> 00:13:09,985
I lied to everyone.

332
00:13:10,019 --> 00:13:11,069
I cheated to get here,

333
00:13:11,104 --> 00:13:12,554
and if you put me in front
of Henry Gerard,

334
00:13:12,572 --> 00:13:13,905
he's not gonna
remember me.

335
00:13:13,940 --> 00:13:15,223
'Cause you never took
his class.

336
00:13:15,241 --> 00:13:16,441
Because I never went
to his class.

337
00:13:16,492 --> 00:13:17,526
'Cause you never went
to Harvard.

338
00:13:17,560 --> 00:13:18,944
- That's not true.
- Bullshit.

339
00:13:18,995 --> 00:13:20,529
Louis, please, look, I know
you have every right to be angry

340
00:13:20,563 --> 00:13:21,663
with me.
I'm not angry.

341
00:13:21,698 --> 00:13:23,898
Angry is just a flash
in the pan.

342
00:13:23,916 --> 00:13:25,500
My outrage is here to stay,

343
00:13:25,535 --> 00:13:27,953
and I will obliterate any
infection threatening my firm.

344
00:13:28,004 --> 00:13:29,588
I'm not the infection
you think I am.

345
00:13:29,622 --> 00:13:33,291
The only thing that's bullshit
is that A -plus!

346
00:13:38,848 --> 00:13:40,349
What?

347
00:13:40,383 --> 00:13:41,416
Louis, I went to Harvard.

348
00:13:41,434 --> 00:13:43,969
I...

349
00:13:44,020 --> 00:13:46,388
I just changed my grade.

350
00:13:46,422 --> 00:13:48,890
You expect me
to believe that?

351
00:13:48,924 --> 00:13:50,142
I have always been
the smartest kid

352
00:13:50,193 --> 00:13:51,943
at every school
that I went to.

353
00:13:51,978 --> 00:13:54,980
High school, college,
the first two years of Harvard,

354
00:13:55,031 --> 00:13:56,314
I'd get "A"s
without studying.

355
00:13:56,366 --> 00:14:00,485
I'd ace every test
without going to class, but--

356
00:14:00,536 --> 00:14:01,570
but that third year...

357
00:14:01,604 --> 00:14:03,121
You had to take Gerard.

358
00:14:03,156 --> 00:14:04,239
I could memorize his books,

359
00:14:04,273 --> 00:14:05,657
but his tests weren't
about his books.

360
00:14:05,708 --> 00:14:07,609
Yeah,
they're about his lectures.

361
00:14:07,627 --> 00:14:09,995
The final exam--
I failed it.

362
00:14:10,046 --> 00:14:11,713
I went to his office to beg
for a second chance.

363
00:14:11,748 --> 00:14:12,781
He doesn't give
second chances.

364
00:14:12,799 --> 00:14:15,584
- I had to try.
- He wouldn't do it.

365
00:14:15,618 --> 00:14:17,753
He wasn't there.

366
00:14:17,787 --> 00:14:19,621
I got to his office.
It was empty.

367
00:14:19,639 --> 00:14:20,972
His computer was
just sitting there,

368
00:14:21,007 --> 00:14:22,424
logged in
to the main system.

369
00:14:22,458 --> 00:14:23,892
He was about to submit
his grades.

370
00:14:23,926 --> 00:14:27,012
I only had a few seconds
before he came back, so...

371
00:14:27,063 --> 00:14:29,765
I decided to save myself.

372
00:14:29,799 --> 00:14:32,467
No, you decided
to give yourself an A-plus.

373
00:14:32,485 --> 00:14:35,020
No, Louis.

374
00:14:35,071 --> 00:14:37,138
You might not be able
to believe me

375
00:14:37,156 --> 00:14:40,475
about anything else
ever again.

376
00:14:40,493 --> 00:14:44,112
Believe this.

377
00:14:44,146 --> 00:14:46,948
You have no idea how much
I wish I could do it over again,

378
00:14:46,982 --> 00:14:49,668
because this time,
I would do it right.

379
00:14:49,702 --> 00:14:52,704
I would go to every class, and I
would attend every lecture,

380
00:14:52,755 --> 00:14:55,657
and I would feast
on what that place has to offer

381
00:14:55,675 --> 00:14:57,592
like no one ever has.

382
00:14:57,627 --> 00:14:59,267
But you didn't do it right
the first time.

383
00:14:59,295 --> 00:15:00,512
You cheated,
and now you're looking at me

384
00:15:00,546 --> 00:15:01,847
to help you get away with it.
No, Louis-

385
00:15:01,881 --> 00:15:03,665
Get out of my sight.

386
00:15:06,647 --> 00:15:09,482
What a surprise.

387
00:15:09,739 --> 00:15:11,640
Louis, please,
I just want to--

388
00:15:11,658 --> 00:15:13,525
I know what you want to do--
you want to lobby me

389
00:15:13,576 --> 00:15:14,910
on behalf of someone
who had the audacity--

390
00:15:14,944 --> 00:15:17,646
I love him.

391
00:15:17,664 --> 00:15:19,031
What?

392
00:15:19,082 --> 00:15:20,582
We're moving in together,
and we're starting

393
00:15:20,617 --> 00:15:22,834
a life together.
Rachel-

394
00:15:22,869 --> 00:15:25,254
and I'm telling you this
because I know what he did

395
00:15:25,288 --> 00:15:28,390
and I still love him.

396
00:15:28,424 --> 00:15:30,559
Okay, here's the problem.

397
00:15:30,593 --> 00:15:32,194
I don't.

398
00:15:32,228 --> 00:15:34,429
- Louis.
- Rachel...

399
00:15:34,464 --> 00:15:36,331
I respect you.

400
00:15:36,349 --> 00:15:37,883
I care about you.

401
00:15:37,934 --> 00:15:40,202
But this isn't about you.

402
00:15:40,236 --> 00:15:43,438
This is about Mike
and what he did to me.

403
00:15:45,692 --> 00:15:46,775
You know,

404
00:15:46,809 --> 00:15:48,843
he came to me the night
that you asked him

405
00:15:48,861 --> 00:15:50,729
to be your associate.

406
00:15:50,780 --> 00:15:52,147
I told him to go with you.

407
00:15:52,181 --> 00:15:53,815
Why?

408
00:15:53,849 --> 00:15:54,866
Because he said he had
a connection with you

409
00:15:54,901 --> 00:15:56,318
that he's never had
with Harvey.

410
00:15:56,352 --> 00:15:57,703
- He said that?
- Yes.

411
00:15:57,737 --> 00:15:59,871
Your shared love of the law.

412
00:15:59,906 --> 00:16:01,873
- Yeah, I told him that.
- I know.

413
00:16:01,908 --> 00:16:03,575
And I have
the same connection with you.

414
00:16:03,626 --> 00:16:06,161
Rachel, you're asking me to--

415
00:16:06,195 --> 00:16:08,196
Louis, he didn't do this
to you.

416
00:16:08,214 --> 00:16:09,894
He did it so that
he can practice the thing

417
00:16:09,916 --> 00:16:11,199
that we all love.

418
00:16:11,217 --> 00:16:14,720
And if you don't let it go,

419
00:16:14,754 --> 00:16:19,174
he's never gonna be able
to practice it again.

420
00:16:26,399 --> 00:16:28,183
Thank you for coming alone.

421
00:16:28,217 --> 00:16:31,103
I'm happy to help,
but Jessica and I are a team,

422
00:16:31,154 --> 00:16:33,405
and asking to see me alone
doesn't change that.

423
00:16:33,439 --> 00:16:35,040
I'm not gonna cut her out
of the process.

424
00:16:35,057 --> 00:16:37,492
Isn't that what
she's doing to me?

425
00:16:39,162 --> 00:16:41,830
She's trying to kill
the sale.

426
00:16:41,864 --> 00:16:43,248
That's not
what this letter says.

427
00:16:43,282 --> 00:16:44,783
I'm not a lawyer,
but I'm not stupid.

428
00:16:44,834 --> 00:16:47,569
It says all communication
goes through Pearson Specter.

429
00:16:47,587 --> 00:16:49,838
- This doesn't kill the deal.
- It tells them that

430
00:16:49,872 --> 00:16:52,073
they've been negotiating with
people with no power at all.

431
00:16:52,091 --> 00:16:53,375
No, it tells them
they have

432
00:16:53,409 --> 00:16:55,711
to negotiate with two entities
instead of just one.

433
00:16:55,745 --> 00:16:58,964
It gives us more firepower.

434
00:16:59,015 --> 00:17:00,682
What do you want, Lisa?

435
00:17:00,717 --> 00:17:02,801
I want to know why your
signature isn't on that letter.

436
00:17:02,852 --> 00:17:04,102
Because we came
to a consensus,

437
00:17:04,137 --> 00:17:06,221
and she signed it
on both our behalves.

438
00:17:06,255 --> 00:17:08,089
- I don't believe you.
- I don't care.

439
00:17:08,107 --> 00:17:09,975
And if you can't handle us
notifying the buyer

440
00:17:10,026 --> 00:17:11,360
that we're evaluating
this sale,

441
00:17:11,394 --> 00:17:12,527
then it makes me question

442
00:17:12,562 --> 00:17:14,146
whose judgment is
really clouded.

443
00:17:14,197 --> 00:17:15,731
Now, if you'll excuse me,

444
00:17:15,765 --> 00:17:17,949
I'm done meeting
behind my partner's back.

445
00:17:20,987 --> 00:17:22,204
What the hell happened
to letting me

446
00:17:22,238 --> 00:17:23,488
evaluate this offer?

447
00:17:23,539 --> 00:17:25,440
I am letting you
evaluate the offer.

448
00:17:25,458 --> 00:17:27,409
You sent this letter
to kill the deal.

449
00:17:27,443 --> 00:17:29,578
I sent that letter
to buy you time.

450
00:17:29,612 --> 00:17:30,796
Jessica, you put my name

451
00:17:30,830 --> 00:17:32,881
on a document you knew
I wouldn't support.

452
00:17:32,915 --> 00:17:36,385
You are on Lisa's side.
You want to sell.

453
00:17:36,419 --> 00:17:39,004
This isn't about Lisa,
and I don't give a shit

454
00:17:39,055 --> 00:17:40,505
whether this company
is sold or not.

455
00:17:40,556 --> 00:17:43,341
This is about you and me and how
we're going to run this firm.

456
00:17:43,393 --> 00:17:44,676
Didn't we just have
a conversation about that?

457
00:17:44,727 --> 00:17:45,761
Yeah, we sure did.

458
00:17:45,795 --> 00:17:46,928
And when it had to do
with Scottie,

459
00:17:46,962 --> 00:17:48,980
you gave me a big speech
about trust,

460
00:17:49,015 --> 00:17:50,899
about how I had to trust
you had rational reasons

461
00:17:50,933 --> 00:17:51,900
for what you were doing.

462
00:17:51,934 --> 00:17:53,985
- This is different.
- Exactly.

463
00:17:54,020 --> 00:17:55,737
This time
it's not personal for me.

464
00:17:55,772 --> 00:17:56,971
It's personal for you.

465
00:17:56,989 --> 00:17:58,356
And you're not playing
by your own rules.

466
00:17:58,408 --> 00:18:00,275
This deal is wrong,
Harvey.

467
00:18:00,309 --> 00:18:02,644
And like it or not,
I'm still the managing partner.

468
00:18:02,662 --> 00:18:03,829
Not on this.

469
00:18:03,863 --> 00:18:05,580
On this,
you're a co-executor,

470
00:18:05,615 --> 00:18:06,748
and you're not putting
my name on any more letters.

471
00:18:06,783 --> 00:18:09,317
So I suggest you get
your head on straight

472
00:18:09,335 --> 00:18:10,702
and look at this deal
rationally.

473
00:18:10,753 --> 00:18:12,204
And if you can't do that,

474
00:18:12,255 --> 00:18:15,791
I suggest you step aside.

475
00:18:15,825 --> 00:18:18,043
Jessica, you loved him.

476
00:18:18,094 --> 00:18:21,096
I know you're hurting.
So is she.

477
00:18:21,130 --> 00:18:24,015
Whatever your history
with her,

478
00:18:24,050 --> 00:18:25,967
so is she.

479
00:18:37,113 --> 00:18:40,565
You're here late.

480
00:18:40,616 --> 00:18:42,317
The life of an associate,
right?

481
00:18:42,351 --> 00:18:45,403
Ah, yeah, I remember.

482
00:18:45,455 --> 00:18:47,706
I used to live in this room,

483
00:18:47,740 --> 00:18:49,541
work piled all around me,

484
00:18:49,575 --> 00:18:52,711
surviving on coffee,
delivery,

485
00:18:52,745 --> 00:18:55,497
and no sleep.

486
00:18:55,531 --> 00:18:56,798
And the whole time,
wondering,

487
00:18:56,833 --> 00:18:59,801
"man, is it ever gonna get
any easier?"

488
00:18:59,836 --> 00:19:01,870
- Does it?
- No.

489
00:19:03,339 --> 00:19:04,639
But you still love it.

490
00:19:04,674 --> 00:19:07,175
And so do you.

491
00:19:07,209 --> 00:19:08,376
Or else you'd be home
with the woman

492
00:19:08,394 --> 00:19:13,565
who loves you,
not spending your night here.

493
00:19:13,599 --> 00:19:16,818
- You know.
- She came to see me.

494
00:19:16,853 --> 00:19:18,052
I didn't think
I could forgive you.

495
00:19:18,070 --> 00:19:21,222
But then somehow,
she...

496
00:19:21,240 --> 00:19:22,574
Made me realize I could.

497
00:19:26,112 --> 00:19:28,229
Louis, I don't know
how to thank you.

498
00:19:28,247 --> 00:19:30,231
Oh, no, no, no.
Don't thank me yet.

499
00:19:30,249 --> 00:19:32,033
I'm not the one
you did this to.

500
00:19:32,067 --> 00:19:33,335
What are you saying?

501
00:19:33,369 --> 00:19:35,420
I'm saying you did this
