a favor.

643
00:25:26,409 --> 00:25:28,226
I doubt the trustees
will care about semantics

644
00:25:28,244 --> 00:25:29,894
when they see that.

645
00:25:29,912 --> 00:25:32,396
Well, I doubt the trustees
are gonna see anything at all.

646
00:25:32,415 --> 00:25:34,332
Because that envelope is full
of blank paper

647
00:25:34,366 --> 00:25:37,118
or your dry cleaning receipts.

648
00:25:37,169 --> 00:25:39,587
You think I'm bluffing?

649
00:25:39,622 --> 00:25:41,039
I know you are.

650
00:25:41,073 --> 00:25:43,091
If you think that envelope
is meaningless.

651
00:25:43,125 --> 00:25:44,486
Why don't you go ahead
and open it?

652
00:25:44,510 --> 00:25:46,795
Your poker face
has gotten much better,

653
00:25:46,846 --> 00:25:47,796
I'll give you that.

654
00:25:47,847 --> 00:25:49,214
A lot of practice,
you know,

655
00:25:49,248 --> 00:25:52,183
compromising my way
through life.

656
00:25:54,520 --> 00:25:56,604
- You know.
- I know.

657
00:25:56,639 --> 00:25:58,640
And you talk a big game,

658
00:25:58,691 --> 00:26:00,275
but you're just as human
as everyone else,

659
00:26:00,309 --> 00:26:02,694
you smug son of a bitch.

660
00:26:04,780 --> 00:26:06,231
What's your favor?

661
00:26:06,265 --> 00:26:08,950
Find a reason to cancel
your trip on Friday.

662
00:26:08,984 --> 00:26:11,369
And if Louis Litt ever tries
to contact you after that,

663
00:26:11,403 --> 00:26:12,937
don't take his call.

664
00:26:12,955 --> 00:26:15,657
- Seems easy enough.
- It is.

665
00:26:15,708 --> 00:26:18,910
Have a good night,
Professor Gerard.

666
00:26:18,944 --> 00:26:22,330
Here's the problem,
Mr. Specter.

667
00:26:22,381 --> 00:26:25,333
I don't only talk a big game.
I walk it.

668
00:26:25,384 --> 00:26:29,921
And ethics is not about
never doing anything wrong.

669
00:26:29,955 --> 00:26:33,224
It's about making choices.

670
00:26:33,259 --> 00:26:37,178
And I'm not going to let you
make my choice for me.

671
00:26:38,630 --> 00:26:41,983
So go do
whatever you're gonna do,

672
00:26:42,017 --> 00:26:44,068
but I'm not canceling
my trip.

673
00:26:59,623 --> 00:27:02,074
- You didn't get it done.
- How'd you know?

674
00:27:02,108 --> 00:27:04,109
Because I know you would call
to tell me if it's okay.

675
00:27:04,127 --> 00:27:06,412
And you didn't call,
so it's not okay.

676
00:27:06,446 --> 00:27:08,631
Then why are you so calm?

677
00:27:08,665 --> 00:27:09,632
Because you've taught me
enough to know

678
00:27:09,666 --> 00:27:12,117
that it's going to be okay.

679
00:27:12,135 --> 00:27:14,970
- It's not.
- What?

680
00:27:15,005 --> 00:27:17,840
It's not gonna be okay.
I don't see what we're gonna do.

681
00:27:17,891 --> 00:27:19,291
What do you mean you don't see
what we're gonna do?

682
00:27:19,309 --> 00:27:20,476
You're Harvey Specter.

683
00:27:20,510 --> 00:27:21,477
What's that
supposed to mean?

684
00:27:21,511 --> 00:27:22,645
It means there's a gun

685
00:27:22,679 --> 00:27:23,679
pointed at our heads.

686
00:27:23,730 --> 00:27:25,964
There's 146 things
that we can do.

687
00:27:25,982 --> 00:27:27,483
We just have to put our heads
together and figure it out.

688
00:27:27,517 --> 00:27:28,817
What the hell do you think
I've been doing

689
00:27:28,852 --> 00:27:30,019
all goddamn night?

690
00:27:30,070 --> 00:27:32,237
