want the same thing

753
00:30:12,982 --> 00:30:15,517
doesn't mean that I'm willing
to perjure myself to get it.

754
00:30:18,971 --> 00:30:20,489
Please.

755
00:30:20,523 --> 00:30:23,075
You said you didn't want
to fail him again.

756
00:30:39,125 --> 00:30:41,126
You didn't fail.

757
00:30:43,129 --> 00:30:46,014
You don't need to make me
feel better.

758
00:30:46,049 --> 00:30:47,099
I'm not trying
to make you feel better.

759
00:30:47,133 --> 00:30:50,469
I'm just telling you
the truth.

760
00:30:50,503 --> 00:30:54,106
You didn't fail because...

761
00:30:54,140 --> 00:30:55,974
We were always playing
on borrowed time.

762
00:30:56,008 --> 00:30:58,527
- Mike.
- Harvey.

763
00:30:58,561 --> 00:31:01,513
I wouldn't have
any of this without you.

764
00:31:01,531 --> 00:31:06,401
I think it's time
I cut your exposure.

765
00:31:06,452 --> 00:31:08,036
You don't have to do that.

766
00:31:08,071 --> 00:31:10,072
It's all gonna come
crashing down anyway.

767
00:31:10,123 --> 00:31:12,407
I'm gonna go to Louis.

768
00:31:12,458 --> 00:31:13,792
I'm going to resign,

769
00:31:13,827 --> 00:31:16,194
and I'm gonna beg him
to let this whole thing go.

770
00:31:18,882 --> 00:31:20,198
Then I'm going with you.

771
00:31:20,216 --> 00:31:21,300
Harvey,

772
00:31:21,334 --> 00:31:25,053
when Trevor went
to Jessica with my secret,

773
00:31:25,088 --> 00:31:28,173
I felt betrayed.

774
00:31:28,207 --> 00:31:32,177
I lost my closest friend
in the world.

775
00:31:32,211 --> 00:31:34,546
And I know you don't like
to admit it,

776
00:31:34,564 --> 00:31:37,566
but we're friends.

777
00:31:39,903 --> 00:31:42,654
And I'm not gonna betray
my friend.

778
00:32:13,866 --> 00:32:16,417
I used to hate
this kind of thing.

779
00:32:16,452 --> 00:32:18,586
- What kind of thing?
- Guest lectures.

780
00:32:18,621 --> 00:32:20,288
Hardman used to make us
sit through them.

781
00:32:21,406 --> 00:32:24,909
Except he gave tests
afterwards.

782
00:32:24,927 --> 00:32:29,747
Yeah, and if you didn't pass,
you got stuck on doc review.

783
00:32:29,765 --> 00:32:31,248
Goddamn Hardman.

784
00:32:32,301 --> 00:32:34,435
You remember
the Robinson case?

785
00:32:34,470 --> 00:32:35,520
Sure do.

786
00:32:35,554 --> 00:32:38,856
80,000 documents,
two years of prep,

787
00:32:38,891 --> 00:32:40,475
and five months in court.

788
00:32:40,526 --> 00:32:42,426
And the Friday
before trial started,

789
00:32:42,444 --> 00:32:45,429
he assigned you and I
to proof everything.

790
00:32:46,482 --> 00:32:48,232
You blew it off.

791
00:32:48,266 --> 00:32:49,484
And you covered for me.

792
00:32:49,535 --> 00:32:51,486
You did your half and mine,
then turned it in.

793
00:32:51,537 --> 00:32:52,487
He would've fired you
on the spot.

794
00:32:52,538 --> 00:32:54,205
Exactly, and I'm here

795
00:32:54,239 --> 00:32:56,291
because you didn't sell out
a friend then,

796
00:32:56,325 --> 00:32:58,293
but you're about to now.

797
00:32:58,327 --> 00:33:00,945
- Mike.
- Me.

798
00:33:00,963 --> 00:33:03,164
Friend?

799
00:33:03,215 --> 00:33:05,282
Louis,
I may not ever say it,

800
00:33:05,301 --> 00:33:06,834
but that's not
because we aren't.

801
00:33:06,885 --> 00:33:08,119
We are.
You know it.

802
00:33:08,137 --> 00:33:10,555
I know it.

803
00:33:10,589 --> 00:33:11,923
I just don't like
to say it.

804
00:33:11,957 --> 00:33:14,142
Last time I asked you,
you said, "don't push it."

805
00:33:14,176 --> 00:33:15,677
You knew I meant yes.

806
00:33:15,728 --> 00:33:17,929
I did.

807
00:33:20,766 --> 00:33:23,651
So Mike told you.
He did.

808
00:33:23,686 --> 00:33:26,354
What'd you say?

809
00:33:26,405 --> 00:33:27,822
Doesn't matter.

810
00:33:27,856 --> 00:33:29,741
Bottom line is I forgave him
because I don't care

811
00:33:29,775 --> 00:33:31,576
what some stupid piece
of paper says.

812
00:33:31,610 --> 00:33:33,161
And I want you
to forgive him too.

813
00:33:33,195 --> 00:33:34,946
Oh, Harvey,
I did forgive him.

814
00:33:34,980 --> 00:33:36,647
I just can't cover it up
for him.

815
00:33:36,665 --> 00:33:38,145
You covered it up
with Hardman for me.

816
00:33:38,150 --> 00:33:39,417
What you did that weekend

817
00:33:39,451 --> 00:33:43,204
is not the same as what he did
to Professor Gerard.

818
00:33:43,255 --> 00:33:45,256
What's the same is
Hardman wouldn't have let it go,

819
00:33:45,290 --> 00:33:46,824
and Gerard won't let it go.

820
00:33:46,842 --> 00:33:48,126
You make Mike confess,

821
00:33:48,160 --> 00:33:50,080
you might as well throw his life
down the toilet.

822
00:33:50,095 --> 00:33:53,881
Harvey,
he didn't just betray us.

823
00:33:53,932 --> 00:33:56,167
He betrayed the law.
He did.

824
00:33:56,185 --> 00:33:58,136
- That's not right.
- It isn't.

825
00:33:58,170 --> 00:34:00,171
But forgiveness isn't
about right and wrong.

826
00:34:00,189 --> 00:34:03,024
Louis, I know you value
the letter of the law,

827
00:34:03,058 --> 00:34:04,475
but what about its spirit?

828
00:34:04,509 --> 00:34:06,444
Because Mike embodies

829
00:34:06,478 --> 00:34:08,696
that spirit
more than either one of us.

830
00:34:08,731 --> 00:34:12,516
You said we're friends.

831
00:34:12,534 --> 00:34:15,019
A friend would not ask me
to do this.

832
00:34:15,037 --> 00:34:17,238
No, Louis.

833
00:34:17,289 --> 00:34:20,191
A friend just won't hold it
against you if you don't.

834
00:34:48,520 --> 00:34:50,438
Do you swear to tell
the truth, the whole truth,

835
00:34:50,489 --> 00:34:52,523
and nothing but the truth,
so help you God?

836
00:34:52,557 --> 00:34:54,025
I do.

837
00:34:54,059 --> 00:34:58,029
But before we start,
I'd like to make a statement.

838
00:34:58,063 --> 00:34:59,781
I am here to tell the truth,

839
00:34:59,832 --> 00:35:01,398
but what I want you
to understand

840
00:35:01,417 --> 00:35:03,501
is that truth is subjective.

841
00:35:03,535 --> 00:35:05,169
The truth is the truth.

842
00:35:05,204 --> 00:35:07,571
No.
The law is the law.

843
00:35:07,589 --> 00:35:10,908
We can define
where a legal line is.

844
00:35:10,926 --> 00:35:12,760
I'm talking about the truth.

845
00:35:24,056 --> 00:35:26,107
The truth is
much more complicated.

846
00:35:26,141 --> 00:35:28,109
By the letter of the law,

847
00:35:28,143 --> 00:35:30,778
Quentin Sainz may
or may not have been competent.

848
00:35:30,813 --> 00:35:34,649
I can't say what's true
with 100% certainty.

849
00:35:34,700 --> 00:35:36,934
I just don't know.

850
00:35:36,952 --> 00:35:38,536
But what I can say
with certainty

851
00:35:38,570 --> 00:35:40,788
is that Quentin knew
what he was doing

852
00:35:40,823 --> 00:35:43,407
when he trusted me to look
after his best interests.

853
00:35:43,441 --> 00:35:44,959
How do you know that?

854
00:35:44,993 --> 00:35:46,327
Because I knew him.

855
00:35:46,378 --> 00:35:49,080
Just because someone
can't check off everything

856
00:35:49,114 --> 00:35:50,948
on the list
that's required

857
00:35:50,966 --> 00:35:52,950
to be competent
doesn't mean

858
00:35:52,968 --> 00:35:56,804
they aren't better at whatever
they do than the rest of us.

859
00:35:56,839 --> 00:35:59,006
And Quentin Sainz
was an amazing man

860
00:35:59,057 --> 00:36:00,791
with an amazing mind.

861
00:36:00,809 --> 00:36:02,560
And if he were here right now,

862
00:36:02,594 --> 00:36:04,295
I'd still listen to him
on any subject

863
00:36:04,313 --> 00:36:06,564
sooner than I'd listen
to anybody else.

864
00:36:06,598 --> 00:36:08,649
That's all very touching,

865
00:36:08,684 --> 00:36:11,319
but we're not here to talk
about the truth.

866
00:36:11,353 --> 00:36:14,272
We're here to deal
with the letter of the law.

867
00:36:14,306 --> 00:36:17,825
Have you never met someone
who by the letter of the law

868
00:36:17,860 --> 00:36:19,777
shouldn't be able to do
what they do?

869
00:36:19,811 --> 00:36:21,913
Who beat the odds?
Your honor-

870
00:36:21,947 --> 00:36:24,165
We are talking
about a man's life.

871
00:36:24,199 --> 00:36:26,501
We are talking
about his legacy.

872
00:36:26,535 --> 00:36:28,619
And I dispute that those things
are less important

873
00:36:28,653 --> 00:36:31,322
than the letter of the law.

874
00:36:39,515 --> 00:36:41,215
Your honor,
what has to happen today

875
00:36:41,266 --> 00:36:42,216
is very clear.

876
00:36:42,267 --> 00:36:44,969
You have to undo
this injustice.

877
00:36:45,003 --> 00:36:48,689
Yes.
This is about justice.

878
00:36:48,724 --> 00:36:51,342
But the issue isn't whether
Quentin Sainz was competent

879
00:36:51,360 --> 00:36:54,178
when he made me executor,
but rather,

880
00:36:54,196 --> 00:36:57,681
would it have been his intent
to do so if he were.

881
00:36:57,699 --> 00:37:00,735
This man dedicated his life
to one thing,

882
00:37:00,786 --> 00:37:03,187
and the circumstances
surrounding how he decided

883
00:37:03,205 --> 00:37:06,690
to protect that thing
is not the question.

884
00:37:06,708 --> 00:37:09,360
It's a question of law,
Ms. Pearson.

885
00:37:09,378 --> 00:37:12,880
No, it is a question
of doing what is right.

886
00:37:12,915 --> 00:37:14,715
Louis.

887
00:37:14,750 --> 00:37:17,835
What the hell
are you doing here?

888
00:37:18,921 --> 00:37:20,371
- I--
- I told you I needed

889
00:37:20,389 --> 00:37:22,473
the Carell filings by lunch--
you didn't get that done,

890
00:37:22,507 --> 00:37:24,725
so now you don't get to listen
to this lecture.

891
00:37:24,760 --> 00:37:27,728
You do not get to listen to this
titan talk about legal ethics.

892
00:37:27,763 --> 00:37:29,063
You know something,
you make me sick.

893
00:37:29,097 --> 00:37:30,264
So do me a quick favor
and tell him you're sorry

894
00:37:30,315 --> 00:37:33,217
and get the hell
out of here.

895
00:37:39,408 --> 00:37:40,391
I'm sorry.

896
00:37:40,409 --> 00:37:43,611
I accept your apology,

897
00:37:43,662 --> 00:37:45,580
but I'm not
the aggrieved one here.

898
00:37:45,614 --> 00:37:49,066
Louis is.

899
00:37:49,084 --> 00:37:52,453
Louis...

900
00:37:52,504 --> 00:37:54,956
I'm sorry.
Yeah.

901
00:38:04,600 --> 00:38:06,968
It's not my pony.
Come on.

902
00:38:07,019 --> 00:38:09,553
Motion to remove Jessica
Pearson as executor denied.

903
00:38:11,773 --> 00:38:14,558
Well, you were right.

904
00:38:14,592 --> 00:38:17,928
Quentin did know
what he was doing.

905
00:38:17,946 --> 00:38:22,116
I know how hard
it must have been...

906
00:38:22,150 --> 00:38:25,102
At the end.

907
00:38:25,120 --> 00:38:27,071
I'm glad Quentin had you.

908
00:38:27,105 --> 00:38:29,273
I'm glad he had you too.

909
00:38:52,797 --> 00:38:55,132
He let it go.

910
00:39:08,697 --> 00:39:10,581
I heard it all worked out.

911
00:39:10,615 --> 00:39:12,917
Never a doubt.

912
00:39:15,871 --> 00:39:17,988
I've got a present for you.

913
00:39:18,006 --> 00:39:20,007
Tiffany.

914
00:39:25,547 --> 00:39:27,664
"D.J.S."

915
00:39:27,683 --> 00:39:29,850
This is a present
for Scottie.

916
00:39:29,885 --> 00:39:31,686
Which makes it a present
for you.

917
00:39:31,720 --> 00:39:34,305
- Let's put this in her office.
- Great.

918
00:39:34,339 --> 00:39:37,558
We can put it next to your
overpriced bottle of scotch.

919
00:39:37,609 --> 00:39:39,143
So it was a great gift.

920
00:39:39,177 --> 00:39:42,513
Now it is.

921
00:39:42,531 --> 00:39:46,033
For the record,
her middle name is Victoria.

922
00:39:46,068 --> 00:39:48,119
No, it isn't.

923
00:39:48,153 --> 00:39:50,121
What is it?

924
00:39:50,155 --> 00:39:52,356
Please, she never told me.

925
00:39:52,374 --> 00:39:53,357
Julie?

926
00:39:53,375 --> 00:39:54,408
- Seriously?
- Jessie?

927
00:39:54,459 --> 00:39:55,659
- Oh, my God.
- Joy?

928
00:39:55,693 --> 00:39:57,194
- You're pathetic.
- Jenny?

929
00:39:57,212 --> 00:40:00,697
Not telling.

930
00:40:00,716 --> 00:40:03,200
I don't think
this is a good idea.

931
00:40:03,218 --> 00:40:04,201
I don't care.

932
00:40:04,219 --> 00:40:05,386
What are they gonna do,
fire us?

933
00:40:05,420 --> 00:40:07,421
Mike, I haven't left
before 5:00

934
00:40:07,472 --> 00:40:09,206
in the past six years.

935
00:40:09,224 --> 00:40:10,508
All the more reason
to do it.

936
00:40:10,542 --> 00:40:12,009
Now what do you want to do?

937
00:40:12,043 --> 00:40:15,229
See a movie, grab dinner,
get a drink?

938
00:40:17,899 --> 00:40:20,884
I just want to go home.

939
00:40:24,689 --> 00:40:26,941
Yeah.
Let's go home.

940
00:40:37,335 --> 00:40:41,088
People seem to keep coming
in here lately.

941
00:40:41,123 --> 00:40:43,874
I needed to hear some music.

942
00:40:43,908 --> 00:40:45,960
And drink some scotch.

943
00:40:46,011 --> 00:40:49,764
How often do you really
do one without the other?

944
00:40:55,437 --> 00:40:57,271
Move over.

945
00:41:16,274 --> 00:41:19,910
Did you take care
of your Marcus problem?

946
00:41:19,944 --> 00:41:23,798
For the time being.

947
00:41:23,832 --> 00:41:26,383
Good.

948
00:41:29,554 --> 00:41:32,923
It wasn't really
a Marcus problem.

949
00:41:34,926 --> 00:41:36,927
I know.

950
00:41:38,346 --> 00:41:39,427
You want to hear the truth?

951
00:41:41,343 --> 00:41:43,575
Not tonight.

952
00:41:44,005 --> 00:41:45,909
That's why I didn't tell you
in the first place.

953
00:41:48,488 --> 00:41:50,189
I know.

